### getBlockingAccess() {#a94804dfc966f82aae7847c415c69d08a}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::optional&lt; TerminatedPath &gt; anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;MemorySSA.cpp&#125;::ClobberWalker::getBlockingAccess (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42; StopWhere, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; ListIndex &gt; &amp; PausedSearches, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; ListIndex &gt; &amp; NewPaused, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; TerminatedPath &gt; &amp; Terminated)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Get an access that keeps us from optimizing to the given phi.

PausedSearches is an array of indices into the Paths array. Its incoming value is the indices of searches that stopped at the last phi optimization target. It&#39;s left in an unspecified state.

If this returns std::nullopt, NewPaused is a vector of searches that terminated at StopWhere. Otherwise, NewPaused is left in an unspecified state.

### tryOptimizePhi() {#aa41c8efa8bfccb832d043d759e56e729}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>OptznResult anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;MemorySSA.cpp&#125;::ClobberWalker::tryOptimizePhi (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryphi">MemoryPhi</a> &#42; Phi, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42; Start, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorylocation">MemoryLocation</a> &amp; Loc)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Try to optimize a phi as best as we can.

Returns a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector</a> of Paths that act as legal clobbers. Note that this won&#39;t return <em>all</em> clobbers.

Phi optimization algorithm tl;dr:
<ul>
<li>Find the earliest def/phi, A, we can optimize to</li>
<li>Find if all paths from the starting memory access ultimately reach A
<ul>
<li>If not, optimization isn&#39;t possible.</li>
<li>Otherwise, walk from A to another clobber or phi, A&#39;.
<ul>
<li>If A&#39; is a def, we&#39;re done.</li>
<li>If A&#39; is a phi, try to optimize it.</li>
</ul></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>


A path is a series of &#123;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a>, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorylocation">MemoryLocation</a>&#125; pairs. A path terminates when a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> that clobbers said <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memorylocation">MemoryLocation</a> is found.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/memoryssa-cpp/#l00764">764</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/memoryssa-cpp">MemorySSA.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### walkToPhiOrClobber() {#a39f6c2e778337977760de8b39efa3426}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>UpwardsWalkResult anonymous&#95;namespace&#123;MemorySSA.cpp&#125;::ClobberWalker::walkToPhiOrClobber (DefPath &amp; Desc, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42; StopAt=nullptr, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/memoryaccess">MemoryAccess</a> &#42; SkipStopAt=nullptr) const</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Walk to the next Phi or Clobber in the def chain starting at Desc.Last.

This will update Desc.Last as it walks. It will (optionally) also stop at StopAt.

This does not test for whether StopAt is a clobber
